The paper deals with memory networks, a popular neural architecture for machine reading comprehension and question answering, which falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes network adaptations, which involves modifying the architecture of the memory network, indicating that it falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also analyzes the reasons for poor results, which involves understanding the behavior of the network, indicating that it falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of attention mechanisms, which is a common technique in neural networks, indicating that it falls under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with reading comprehension, which involves understanding text and images, indicating that it falls under the computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV) sub-category.
